The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                 
	New Delhi: India are down three slots to 148th spot in the latest Fifa rankings issued on Wednesday. Bob Houghtons team has suffered due to not playing any internationals recently. They last took the field in the unsuccessful first round qualifiers for the 2010 World Cup against Lebanon. The top 10 in the overall rankings remain unchanged with Argentina, Brazil and Italy occupying the first three places.             
	Parma: Parma hired Hector Cuper on Tuesday as manager for the last 11 games, hoping to save the Italian Serie A team from relegation.    
	Cuper replaces Domenico Di Carlo, who was fired on Monday, the day after Parma lost to Sampdoria to suffer their 12th defeat of the season and sink to 17th place in the 20-team first division. Cuper arrives from Spains Real Betis, which he managed until December when he was fired with the team in 19th place in the 20-team league.         
	Washington: World No. 6 Andy Roddick has decided to miss this years Olympic Games in Beijing to defend his Washington Open title. Both events take place in August and Roddick wants to remain in his home country to help his build-up for the US Open which begins two weeks later. My goal every summer is to win the US Open, the 25-year-old American said in a statement released on Tuesday.    
